## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Razorpay + Expo Go Incompatibility**
> `react-native-razorpay` requires **native code** and does NOT work in Expo Go. Two options:
> - **Option A (Recommended for demo):** Use `expo-linking` to open a Razorpay WebView-based checkout — works in Expo Go, no native build needed.
> - **Option B (Production):** Use `react-native-razorpay` with `npx expo prebuild` + custom dev build (`npx expo run:android`). Expo Go will no longer work.
>
> **I recommend Option A** for your timeline. Which do you prefer?

> [!WARNING]
> **Push Notifications + Expo Go**
> Remote push notifications (`expo-notifications`) do NOT work in Expo Go on Android since SDK 53. They require a development build.
> **Plan:** I'll implement `expo-notifications` for local notifications (which DO work in Expo Go) and structure the code so FCM works when you switch to a dev build later. For now, booking/payment confirmations will use local notifications.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Navigation Restructure**
> The current app uses a flat `StackNavigator`. To add BookingsScreen, Admin, and role-based tabs, I need to wrap the main flow in a **Bottom Tab Navigator**. Tabs will be:
> - 🏠 Home (Map + Search)
> - 📋 Bookings (All/Live/Past)
> - 👤 Profile (Logout + user info)
> - 🔧 Admin (only visible if role is "admin" or "superadmin")
>
> The Stack navigator will remain for detail screens (ParkingDetail → BookingConfirmation → ETicket → Receipt).

